            <text>
                <body>
                    <div type="edition">
                        <div type="textpart">
                            <ab>Il <rs key="#Bishops">vescovo</rs> di Lucca <persName
                            ref="#people/213" key="#Bishops">Pietro</persName> siede in giudizio hic
                            <rs key="#Cities">civitate</rs>
                        <placeName ref="#places/4"
                            key="#Cities #Laubia/topia #Walls #Mother_churches #Bishops"
                            >Luca</placeName> in <rs key="#Fruits/vegetables">broilo</rs> sub <rs
                            key="#Laubia/topia">lopia</rs>, vicino al <rs key="#Walls">muro</rs>
                        della <orgName key="#Mother_churches" ref="#juridical_persons/68"><rs
                                key="#Mother_churches">chiesa</rs> di San Martino</orgName>;
                        assistono, fra gli altri, l’arcidiacono Adalberto, i preti cardinali
                        Eripaldo, Teudimundo, Ropperto, Sicardo, Ropprando, i preti Martino e
                        Pietro, il suddiacono Romaldo, gli scabini Ghisalfridi e Adalperto, i notai
                        Giorgio, Cosperto e Tassimanno, <persName><name ref="Isembaldus"
                                >Isimbaldo</name></persName> e <persName><name ref="Gausfredus"
                                >Cosfridi</name></persName>. Si presenta da una parte l’<rs
                            key="#Archpriests">arciprete e visdomino</rs>
                        <persName key="#Archpriests"><name ref="Viventius"
                            >Vivenzio</name></persName> per conto dello stesso vescovato, dall’altra
                        il <rs key="#Priests">prete</rs>
                        <persName key="#Priests"><name ref="Gisbertus">Ghisperto</name></persName>
                        del <persName>fu <name ref="Auripertus">Auriperto</name></persName>, in lite
                        fra loro: secondo il visdomino, il prete entrò nella <orgName
                            key="#Baptismal_churches" ref="#juridical_persons/265"><rs
                                key="#Baptismal_churches">pieve</rs> di San Gervasio sita loco
                                <placeName key="#Baptismal_churches" ref="#places/185"
                                >Verriana</placeName></orgName> e nelle sue dipendenze e sottrasse
                        oblationem et fruges, tanto lui quanto homines quas ipse trasmisi, e giunse
                        in sua potestatem malo ordine; il prete contraddice questa affermazione.
                        L’arcidiacono interroga il visdomino, domandando se può provare la sua
                        affermazione con testimoni; avuta risposta negativa e ricevuta garanzia dal
                        visdomino, fa giurare al prete di non aver commesso il fatto. L’arciprete
                        chiede allora al prete se possiede ordinationem aut electionem vel qualibet
                        scriptionem aut firmitatem grazie alla quale può contendere alla pieve casis
                        et rebus a essa dipendenti; il prete ammette di non avere alcun documento
                        scritto e che quindi nichild mihi exinde nec pertinuit nec pertinet. Si
                        chiede al <rs key="#Writer #Notary">notaio</rs>
                        <persName key="#Writer #Notary"><name ref="Gausbertus"
                            >Cosperto</name></persName> la scrittura della notitia. <rs
                            key="#Witness">Testimoni</rs> sottoscrittori: <persName
                            key="#Witness #Priests #Cardinals"><name ref="Eribaldus"
                            >Eripaldo</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Priests">presbiter</rs> et <rs key="#Cardinals">cardinalis</rs>,
                            <persName key="#Witness #Priests #Cardinals"><name ref="Teudemundus"
                                >Teudimundo</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Priests">presbiter</rs> et <rs key="#Cardinals">cardinalis</rs>,
                            <persName key="#Witness #Priests #Cardinals"><name ref="Ropprandus"
                                >Ropprando</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Priests">presbiter</rs> et <rs key="#Cardinals">cardinalis</rs>,
                            <persName key="#Witness #Priests #Cardinals"><name ref="Robertus"
                                >Ropperto</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Priests">presbiter</rs> et <rs key="#Cardinals">cardinalis</rs>,
                            <persName key="#Witness #Priests #Cardinals"><name ref="Sicardus"
                                >Sicardo</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Priests">presbiter</rs> et <rs key="#Cardinals">cardinalis</rs>,
                            <persName key="#Witness #Archdeacons"><name ref="Adalbertus"
                                >Adalberto</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Archdeacons">archidiaconus</rs>, <persName key="#Witness #Priests"
                                ><name ref="Petrus">Pietro</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Priests">presbiter</rs>, <persName key="#Witness #Priests"><name
                                ref="Martinus">Martino</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Priests">presbiter</rs>, <persName key="#Witness #Subdeacons"
                                ><name ref="Romaldus">Romaldo</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Subdeacons">subdiaconus</rs>, <persName
                            key="#Witness #Notary #Scabini"><name ref="Giselfredus"
                                >Ghisalfridi</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs> et <rs key="#Scabini">schabinus</rs>,
                            <persName key="#Witness #Notary #Scabini"><name ref="Adalbertus"
                                >Adalperto</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs> et <rs key="#Scabini">schabinus</rs>,
                            <persName key="#Witness #Notary"><name ref="Tassimannus"
                                >Tassimanno</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs>, <persName key="#Witness #Notary"><name
                                ref="Georgius">Giorgio</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs>.</ab>
                        </div>
                    </div>
